SIMPLE: windward
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Windward
<hw>Wind"ward</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The point or side
from which the wind blows; <as>as, to ply to the <ex>windward</ex></as>;
-- opposed to <ant>leeward</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To lay an anchor to the windward</b></col>, <cd>a
figurative expression, signifying to adopt precautionary or anticipatory
measures for success or security.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Windward</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Windward
<hw>Wind"ward</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Situated toward the point from
which the wind blows; <as>as, the <ex>Windward</ex>
Islands</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Windward</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Windward
<hw>Wind"ward</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Toward the wind; in the
direction from which the wind blows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Windy</ent>⟦br⟧
